      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STEREOPHONIC (4) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (22.58) at this track over 400m. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Overdue and is among the main hopes. CURMUDGEON (7) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Gosford over 388m behind Trunkey Nell (23.00) in a Maiden. Was in the money prior to that. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can figure in the finish. ZIPPING EMILY (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fifth (23.95) in a Maiden at The Gardens. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. One of the better chances. CHRONIC FLUFFY (3) is a newcomer from the Dale Wright kennel. Profiles well so pay to keep very safe.",
